 Identify a good loop invariant for the following function. The function is given an integer, then calculates the sum of the digits of that integer. You do not need to prove your loop invariant.
  int sumofdigits(unsigned int n) {
      int ans = 0;
      for (int i = 0; n > 0; i++) {
          ans += n % 10;
n /= 10; }
return ans;
